<Alert type="info">The original MANTRA dataset includes both 2-manifolds and 3-manifolds. AHORN lists them as two separate datasets, with this page focusing on the 3-manifolds. You can find the 2-manifolds dataset [here](/dataset/MANTRA-2-manifolds).</Alert>

The MANTRA collection provides simplicial complexes built from triangulations of closed 2- and 3-manifolds.
Each manifold is represented by its vertex set and list of simplices (triangles or tetrahedra), enabling topological and combinatorial experiments across two dimensions.

Each network is enriched with the following network-level metadata:
- `betti_numbers`, e.g., `[1, 0, 0, 1]`
- `torsion_coefficients`, e.g, `["", "", "Z_2", ""]`
- `name`
- `genus`
- `orientable`
- `vertex_transitive`

This dataset is derived from version 0.0.16 of [MANTRA](https://aidos.group/mantra/).
